# Minor School Esoterica
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Minor School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Abjuration: You gain a competence bonus on dispel checks equal to 1/2 your master specialist level.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Abjurer
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Minor School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Conjuration: Any creature you summon or call appears with extra hit points equal to your caster level.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Conjurer
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Minor School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Divination: Divination spells you cast that have a duration of concentration remain in effect for a number of extra rounds equal to 1/2 your master specialist level after you cease concentrating. You can cast other spells and otherwise act normally during this duration.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Diviner
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Minor School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Enchantment: Targets of your charm spells do not gain a bonus on their saves due to being currently threatened or attacked by you or your allies. In addition, subjects of your compulsion spells do not get a bonus on saves due to being forced to take an action against their natures.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Enchanter
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Minor School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Evocation: When casting an evocation spell, you gain a bonus on Concentration checks equal to 1/2 your master specialist level.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Evoker
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Minor School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Illusion: The save DCs of your illusion spells that have a saving throw entry of "Will disbelief" increase by 2.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Illusionist
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Minor School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Necromancy: When you cast a necromancy spell, undead allies within 60 feet gain turn resistance and a bonus on saves equal to your master specialist level for a number of rounds equal to your master specialist level.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Necromancer
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Minor School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Transmutation: When a transmutation spell you have cast is successfully dispelled, it remains in effect for 1 round and then ends as normal for dispelling. If a creature is responsible for the dispelling effect, it knows that the spell has been dispelled but is functioning for another round.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Transmuter

# Moderate School Esoterica
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Moderate School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Abjuration: If you are subject to a spell that has a partial or half effect on a successful save, you suffer no adverse effect if you successfully save.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Abjurer
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Moderate School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Conjuration: Dispel checks made against your conjuration spells treat your caster level as if it were 5 higher than normal.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Conjurer
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Moderate School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Divination: You gain uncanny dodge (PH SO) for the duration of the spell.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Diviner
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Moderate School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Enchantment: You can immediately reroll any failed Will save against an enchantment or mind-affecting spell or ability; you must accept the result of the second roll.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Enchanter
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Moderate School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Evocation: You gain resistance 20 to any one energy type that matches a descriptor used by the spell you just cast.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Evoker
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Moderate School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Illusion: You gain concealment.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Illusionist
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Moderate School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Necromancy: You are immune to ability damage, ability drain, energy drain, and negative levels.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Necromancer
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Moderate School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Transmutation: You can immediately reroll any failed Fortitude save against a transmutation spell or ability; you must accept the result of the second roll.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Transmuter

# Major School Esoterica
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Major School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Abjuration: When casting an abjuration spell that normally has a range of personal, you can instead choose to cast it as a touch spell that affects a single creature. When casting an abjuration spell that is an emanation centered on you, you can instead choose to cast it as a touch spell that emanates from the touched creature.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Abjurer
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Major School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Conjuration: You can cast a conjuration spell with a casting time of 1 standard action as a swift action.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Conjurer
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Major School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Divination: When you cast a divination spell, you also gain true seeing (as the spell) for 5 rounds.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Diviner
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Major School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Enchantment: Any creature that successfully saves against one of your enchantment spells must save again 1 round later (as if you had cast the spell again) with a +5 bonus on the save.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Enchanter
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Major School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Evocation: Any creature that fails its save against one of your evocation spells takes damage again 1 round later equal to half the damage it took when you cast the spell.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Evoker
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Major School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Illusion: You can cast any illusion spell as a stilled and silent spell and eschew the materials (per the Still Spell, Silent Spell, and Eschew Materials feats) without an increase in caster level or casting time.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Illusionist
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Major School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Necromancy: When you cast a necromancy spell, undead allies within 60 feet gain fast healing 10 for 5 rounds.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Necromancer
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Master Specialist ~ Major School Esoterica.MOD	DESC: Transmutation: When a creature successfully saves against a transmutation spell you cast, it takes damage equal to the level of the spell.|PRESUBCLASS:1,Transmuter

